r “members” for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the United States Code. In clause (5), the words “the provisions applicable to the Office of Personnel Management and the President under” are omitted as surplus. In clause (7), the words “the provisions applicable to performance awards under” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “officer or employee” are substituted for “member” for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the Code.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d), the words “Employees in . . . the personnel system established under” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbcf300aa-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbcf300ab-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/323"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–323","children":[],"tail":" struck out “(d),” after “731(c),”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (a)(3)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/271"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–271","children":[],"tail":" amended subpar. (B) generally. Prior to amendment, subpar. (B) read as follows: “adjusted at the same time and to the same extent as rates in the Senior Executive Service under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5382"},"text":"section 5382 of title 5","children":[],"tail":" are adjusted;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (a)(7), (8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/303"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–303","children":[],"tail":" added par. (7) and redesignated former par. (7) as (8)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/326"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–326","children":[],"tail":" inserted “(e)(1),” after “(d),”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbcf300ac-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idbcf300ad-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"General Accounting Office redesignated Government Accountability Office. See ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/271/s8"},"text":"section 8 of Pub. L. 108–271","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s702"},"text":"section 702 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbcf300ae-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2004 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/271/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 108–271","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2005","children":[],"tail":", and applicable in the case of any annual pay adjustment taking effect on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2005","children":[],"